; Walter de Berchelai or Berkelai was Chamberlain of Scotland in 1165. It was long assumed that they were from the family that held Berkeley Castle in Gloucestershire, but the historian G. W. S. Barrow (1973, <i>The Kingdom of the Scots</i>) adduced evidence that they are more probably from Berkley in Somerset."]},{"name":"Berkley","meanings":["English: variant of   Berkeley  . Compare Scottish   Barclay  .","Jewish (Ashkenazic): assimilated form of   Berkowitz  ."]}]},{"name":"Walter","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old French personal name of Germanic (Frankish) origin, derived from <i>wald</i> ‘rule’ + <i>heri</i>, <i>hari</i> ‘army’. This was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to England, superseding the native Old English form, <i>Wealdhere</i>. It was a very popular name in medieval England, normally pronounced ‘Water’."],"variants":[{"name":"Walther","meanings":["from <i>wald</i> ‘rule’ + <i>heri</i> ‘army’; name of the famous medieval minnesinger  Walther von der Vogelweide  (  <i>c.</i>1170– <i>c.</i>1230 )."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Walter de Berkeley was born in 1136, in Gartly, Banffshire, Scotland, United Kingdom. He married Eva mac Uhtred in 1166. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died in 1193, at the age of 57."},"et":{"1136–1193":"1136–1193","1150–Female":"1150–Surnud","1171–1200":"1171–1200","1136":"1136","1200":"1200","1166":"1166","Abt 1171":"umbes 1171","1150":"1150","1193":"1193","1171":"1171","Gatley, Stockport, Greater Manchester, England":"Gatley, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Gartley, Banffshire, Scotland":"Gartly, Banffshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1136–1193":"1136–1193","1150–Female":"1150–Kuollut","1171–1200":"1171–1200","1136":"1136","1200":"1200","1166":"1166","Abt 1171":"noin 1171","1150":"1150","1193":"1193","1171":"1171","Gatley, Stockport, Greater Manchester, England":"Gatley, Cheshire, Englanti, Y